The paper discusses the use of a neural network for symbolic representation and planning, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of unsupervised learning and image-based domains suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The planning aspect of the paper may also relate to robotics (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY).
